# BLOCKING since Run F2 (OQ-13/OQ-11): flipped on when coordinator/transport/ landed.
# Scoped to the framework-free F2 logic (transport/proto/) via the Makefile's TIDY_FILES + the
# HeaderFilterRegex below. transport/vendor/ (Victor's reference source) and the Arduino-coupled
# transport/hw/ are NOT linted (blanket tidy over framework code is noise). core/ is deferred from the
# blocking scope this PR (pre-existing performance-enum-size findings would need core/ edits — out of
# F2's transport-only boundary; extend in a follow-up core PR).
#
# bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters is disabled: it fires on ordinary multi-string/int signatures
# (telnet_run, build_write_file_cmd, …) and is widely treated as noise, not a real-bug signal.
Checks: >
  clang-analyzer-*,
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters
WarningsAsErrors: 'clang-analyzer-*,bugprone-*,performance-*'
HeaderFilterRegex: 'firmware/coordinator/transport/proto/.*'
